news.title: NGT raps Noida authority for issuing partial OCs to builders without functional STPs
news.para: "We are informed that partial occupancy certificates are issued to facilitate the builders to sell the flats which prima facie amount to offence," the bench said.

news.title: China's Shimao Group plans to use own funds to pay onshore bonds
news.para: Shanghai Shimao Co also said it will be difficult to meet its 38 billion yuan ($5.96 billion) full-year sales target, as sales in the first 11 months were 28.2 billion yuan.

news.title: Adani bid for Radius Estates approved by 80% of creditors
news.para: Debenture holders oppose Adani bid citing 90% ‘haircut’, may approach NCLAT.

news.title: Ashoka Builders India buys 10 acres land in Hyderabad for Rs 235 crore
news.para: "We plan to further invest around Rs 250 crore to develop this mixed-use community, taking the valuation of the project, after completion, to be roughly Rs 600 crore," said Ajitesh Korupolu, CEO, ASBL.

news.title: Land made available for Corridor II of Patna metro rail
news.para: The required land for Corridor II of the project was transferred to Patna Metro Rail Corporation Limited (PMRC) and a no-objection certificate was also acquired from the departments concerned.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals eight homes in Lambha for lack of BU permission
news.para: The civic body’s town planning and estate department sealed three houses behind Swapna Sakar Residency and five houses in Miranagar near Indiranagar 2 Society in Lambha.

news.title: Gurugram: MCG commissioner asks officials to check flaws in civic infra at Sushant Lok-1
news.para: The directions to evaluate if water pipelines and sewer lines need repair or replacement were given at the House meeting after the issues were raised by the councillor of ward number 32, Arti Yadav.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Pay property tax early, get interest rebate
news.para: According to this formula, those who pay their property tax in January 2022 will get an 80% tax interest rebate for residential properties and 60% rebate on interest for non-residential properties.

news.title: 830 bungalows built in Madh Island by forging maps: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: Thorat said 102 maps have been changed to show 830 permanent structures. All these structures (essentially bungalows) have come up on government land marked as No-Development Zone. The plots also fall in the Coastal Regulation Zone.

news.title: MahaRERA can decide payout for mental agony to flat buyers
news.para: The order was passed on a complaint by Sanjay and Shailaja Gaikwad who sought not only direction to Omkar Realtors and Developers to hand over possession of the flat and to pay interest for delayed possession, but also Rs 2 crore compensation for the “mental torture and agony” caused to them.

news.title: Gurugram: 21 unauthorised houses sealed in Sushant Lok-1
news.para: Similarly, developers of seven illegal colonies, spread over 35 acres of agricultural land, were served notices by the enforcement wing of DTCP for violations of the Urban Area Act.

news.title: Faridabad: Conman arrested for duping over 500 people in land fraud
news.para: Joint commissioner (EOW) Chhaya Sharma said the accused, Sudhir Bidhuri (38), was a resident of Tughlaqabad. He started off as a small-time property dealer and later joined a reality firm and started duping people.

news.title: Tata, Siemens group consortium to develop Pune metro line 3
news.para: The 23.3-km elevated metro line connects the Hinjewadi Rajiv Gandhi Infotech Park with Shivajinagar via Balewadi in the second largest city in Maharashtra.

news.title: Haryana to launch portal to analyse hourly air pollution data from C&D sites in January
news.para: The portal, with video fencing with remote connectivity and a live dashboard for easy monitoring, will be operational within a week, said HSPCB secretary S Narayana.

news.title: J&K government sign MoUs worth Rs 18,900 crore with builders
news.para: Manoj Sinha, Lieutenant Governor of Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir predicted that it is likely to receive close to Rs 60,000 crore of investment in real estate sector in very near future since the government has top priority to transform this sector which would have multiplier effects on the UT's economy.
